rComments: Easiest Lin exam I've done so far! Exam (40%) and 3 assignments (60%). Assignments are very easy, but I encourage you to discuss your answers with classmates. Exam was cumulative & open book (everything was from the slides lol) do don't worry. I went over the slides a day before and I was good to go. The prof is very kind too!

I'm not sure what this course would've been like normally, but Simone made an effort to make things easier by making assessments open book. There's a fair bit of content but she taught it in a very straightforward way. She was very friendly and all her evaluations were reasonable.

This is a tough intro-course in general. Prof is fair, makes an effort to help. This is not a bird course, so don't expect to pass it with ease. I'm in 2nd year taking this class, a lot of people are in 1st year thinking they can pass easily without prep.

Very monotone voice, doesn't seem too happy to be teaching, constant interruptions with her internet, with technology, things not being charged. Not prepared at all. Trick questions on her reaching quizzes which change the meaning of the question completely so you're heavily tricked in what the answer might be.

you ask her a question and she either says "i don't know" or doesn't give you a clear answer. for this class specifically you need to be able to talk because it's based on sounds and she doesn't do a very good job at interacting with the students. I wish I didn't have her as my prof, as I want to cry everyday because of her.
